config ZMK_KSCAN_AKII_TWOTIER
    bool "AKII two-tier MCP23017 kscan driver"
    default y if DT_HAS_ZMK_KSCAN_AKII_TWOTIER_ENABLED
    # depends on (not select) KSCAN: ZMK_KSCAN already selects KSCAN (default y)
    # and provides CONFIG_KSCAN_INIT_PRIORITY. `select KSCAN` here creates a
    # Kconfig recursive-dependency loop (KSCAN subtree -> GPIO kscan -> I2C),
    # so we depend on it instead.
    depends on I2C && KSCAN
    help
      Custom two-tier keyboard scanner for the AKII board's 2x MCP23017 I2C
      expanders, talked to over raw I2C (no gpio-controller driver).

      ACTIVE: full matrix scan every active-poll-period-ms -> stock feel.
      IDLE:   after idle-timeout-ms of no activity, drive all rows low and do a
              cheap "any column pulled low?" summary read every
              idle-poll-period-ms; any key down jumps back to ACTIVE.

      Gets idle current down to the slow-poll floor (~0.4mA on this board)
      while keeping typing latency at the active-scan rate.
